The paper describes a new approach to estimating relative risks in time-to-event prediction problems with censored data using deep nonlinear representations of input covariates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions experimentation on multiple real-world datasets with different levels of censoring, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and statistics (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the competing risks scenario, which suggests that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
